473 Legislature in 2027.'
8 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
9 number to read consecutively.
10 SUMMARY
1111 This amendment replaces the bill with a resolve requiring the Department of Health
1122 and Human Services to initiate a rate determination process for developing rates for doula
1133 services under the MaineCare program. The department shall establish a doula council to
1144 provide advice on issues related to reimbursement, credentialing, recruitment, billing and
1155 outreach. The department shall submit a report, no later than February 1, 2027, to the joint
1166 standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over health and human services
1177 matters that includes the department's progress on developing rates and recommendations
1188 for reimbursement of doula services under the MaineCare program. The committee is
1199 authorized to report out legislation related to the report to the 133rd Legislature in 2027.
